derstood&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brett:&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;At the beginning of &lt;em&gt;The Fabric of Reality&lt;/em&gt;, David Deutsch presents this idea that you don&amp;rsquo;t need to know every single fact to fundamentally understand everything that can be understood.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
